<TEXT>
a greyhound bus driving through a spring 
snowstorm overturned and slid down an embankment injuring 16 
people and in cincinnati snow fell sunday for the first time in 
may in nearly a century 
snow also fell in parts of new york pennsylvania west virginia 
and ohio in rochester ny 101 inches of snow fell breaking 
that citys snowfall record for may by more than 6 inches 
the unusual spring storm dumped up to 2 inches of icy slush on 
this northern ohio city and was blamed for the bus accident 
saturday that left three people hospitalized sunday 
thirteen other people including driver james rogers jr were 
treated at two hospitals for minor cuts and bruises and released 
said highway patrol sgt dale meyer 
rains and light snow abruptly changed to a heavy mix of snow and 
sleet and quickly covered ohio route 2 along lake erie just west of 
sandusky when the accident occurred around 830 pm saturday 
meyer said 
ive never seen anything like the weather last night in 
may meyer said it was an isolated condition a snow and sleet 
downpour within a matter of seconds it seemed like you had two 
inches of slush on the road rogers was trying slow the bus by 
downshifting when it spun 180 degrees in the road flipped onto its 
left side and slid gently down the 20foot road embankment meyer 
said 
in cincinnati overnight temperatures dipped into the low to 
mid30s snow saturday and sunday came exactly 91 years after the 
city recorded its last measurable snowfall in may 
</TEXT>
