<TEXT>
irans abadan oil refinery once the 
worlds largest resumed exports saturday after an eightyear gap 
the official islamic republic news agency reported 
the agency monitored in nicosia said a 10000ton shipment of 
fuel oil from the refinery left bandar mahshahr port but did not 
say where it was headed 
the refinery located only a few miles from the border with 
iraq shut down soon after the iraniraq war broke out in september 
1980 
the 3200acre complex was heavily shelled by iraqi artillery 
during the war more than 150 personnel were killed and lost 
production was estimated at 9 billion 
around 6000 technicians and specialists started roundtheclock 
repair work immediately after a united nationssponsored ceasefire 
halted the gulf war aug 20 
production resumed april 1 with an initial capacity of 130000 
barrels a day of oil products irna said 
capacity is expected to rise later this year and reach 360000 
barrels a day in the next two to three years before the war the 
refinery produced 650000 barrels a day 
following repairs of war damage at irans six other refineries 
the countrys total refinery capacity is currently estimated at 
850000 barrels a day 
