a strong earthquake sunday struck a region of 
southwest china where 730 people were killed by a temblor in 
november but this time officials said only about 10 people were 
injured 
sundays quake collapsed some houses and opened rifts in some 
streets in gengma county in yunnan province the official xinhua 
news agency said 
xinhua said there were no reports of deaths or injuries but the 
central seismology bureau in beijing quoted local authorities as 
saying about 10 people were injured four seriously 
the quake measured 63 on the richter scale signifying a quake 
capable of causing severe damage the nov 6 quake that shook 
gengma and devastated nearby counties was more than 10 times 
stronger measuring 76 
that quake chinas worst in 12 years destroyed several 
villages in menglian and lancang counties 90 miles south of 
gengma xinhua said menglian and lancang were shaken by the new 
quake that hit at 938 am sunday 
all three counties are in a remote mountainous region near the 
burmese border that is prone to quakes gengma is largely inhabited 
by members of the va and dai minorities most of whom farm 
more than 1300 aftershocks were recorded in less than two weeks 
after the nov 6 quake seismologists said after that quake that 
the region had entered a new period of quake activity 
the richter scale is a gauge of the energy released by an 
earthquake as measured by ground motion recorded on a seismograph 
each increase of a digit indicates a 10fold increase in severity 
