eight carnivalgoers trapped in a broken super 
loop ride were rescued sunday after being left dangling upside 
down and 60 feet in the air for more than two hours 
apparently a light fixture had shaken loose and had come down 
on the tracks and jammed when the little train came by it was 
stopped said fire department spokesman john mulligan 
the ride in queens which was part of a traveling carnival and 
consists of connecting train cars that run on a hoopshaped track 
ground to a halt late saturday at the top of the loop leaving the 
eight thrillseekers screaming for help 
after a while the trapped riders tiring of being upside down 
unbuckled their seat belts and sat on the safety cage surrounding 
the seats rescue workers feared it might not hold their weight 
mulligan said 
around 1215 am after about 2 hours firefighters using a 
cherry picker were able to take the passengers off the crippled 
ride two at a time he said 
no one was seriously injured but two riders were taken to 
peninsula general hospital for treatment for exposure mulligan 
said 
