seven inches of snow fell in batavia and warsaw ny and snow 
broke tree limbs and downed power lines throughout the western 
finger lakes 
the unusual weather was caused by low pressure centered over 
extreme southcentral quebec that drew moist cold air south across 
the ohio valley and appalachian mountains snow fell over parts of 
new york pennsylvania west virginia and ohio 
by early afternoon temperatures had risen above freezing over 
most of the area and the snow was either mixed with rain or changed 
to rain 
